.Dd June 26, 2026
.Dt VMDKMOUNT 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm vmdkmount
.Nd mounts a VMware Virtual Disk (VMDK) image file
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm vmdkmount
.Op Fl X Ar extended_options
.Op Fl hvV
.Ar source
.Ar mount_point
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm vmdkmount
is a utility to mount a VMware Virtual Disk (VMDK) image file
.Pp
.Nm vmdkmount
is part of the
.Nm libvmdk
package.
.Nm libvmdk
is a library to access the VMware Virtual Disk (VMDK) format
.Pp
.Ar source
a VMware Virtual Disk (VMDK) image file
.Ar mount_point
the directory to serve as mount point
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h
shows this help
.It Fl v
verbose output to stderr, while vmdkmount will remain running in the foreground
.It Fl V
print version
.It Fl X Ar extended_options
extended options to pass to sub system
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
.Sh FILES
None
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
# vmdkmount image.vmdk
vmdkmount 20260626
.sp
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Errors, verbose and debug output are printed to stderr when verbose output \
\-v is enabled.
Verbose and debug output are only printed when enabled at compilation.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr vmdkinfo 1
